---
import CushionIcon from "@/assets/cushion.svg";
---

<header
  class="py-20 lg:py-32 xl:py-52 px-5 flex flex-col justify-start items-start text-left animate-in fill-mode-backwards fade-in slide-in-from-bottom-4 duration-500 ease-out delay-200 md:justify-center md:items-center md:text-center"
>
  <h1
    class="text-xl max-w-prose xl:text-2xl xl:leading-[1.66em] xl:tracking-[-0.015em] xl:text-balance"
  >
    <span class="block md:hidden"
      >Rob Hough is an independent design engineer based in the English
      countryside. Partnering with B2B startups, his work focuses on performant
      and engaging customer experiences.</span
    >
    <span class="block md:hidden mt-4"
      >He also co-runs <a
        href="https://cushion.so"
        class="text-accent underline-offset-2 underline"
        target="_blank">cushion.so</a
      > an async alternative to Slack for distributed teams.</span
    >
    <div class="hidden md:block">
      <span>Rob Hough is an independent design engineer based in the</span>
      <span>English countryside. </span>
      <span
        >Partnering with B2B startups, his work focuses on performant and
        engaging customer experiences.</span
      >
      <span>He also co-runs</span>
      <a
        href="https://cushion.so"
        target="_blank"
        class="group focus rounded-lg"
      >
        <div
          class="relative hidden align-middle size-8 rounded-full mx-0.5 shadow-md bg-black bg-gradient-to-t from-black to-gray-12 text-white scale-100 transition-all will-change-auto duration-200 ease-out group-hover:scale-110 dark:to-gray-3 md:inline-block"
        >
          <div class="absolute inset-0 grid place-items-center scale-125">
            <CushionIcon />
          </div>
        </div>
        <span class="text-accent underline-offset-2 underline">cushion.so</span>
      </a>
      <span>, an async alternative to Slack for distributed teams.</span>
    </div>
  </h1>
</header>
